column5: Was flicking through the channels and came to CNN and they are showing the flooding out there.  Incredible!  As for the flood levels in King / Chehalis, WA, they said a major flood level is 65 feet.  They have reached levels of 75 feet.  A record level.  Previous record was about 70 feet back in 1996.  So far only 2 people reported "missing".  Lets hope and pray they turn out to be ok.
Great my step son just moved out to BC this morning.
